                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName>
                                        <date>26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Novr. 5611</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>My dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">A few days ago I received your letter of<lb/> the
                                                  <date>26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> August</date> last,
                                        the detention of which has been owing to<lb/> some accident
                                        having happened to the “<placeName>Kingston</placeName>”
                                        which necessitated<lb/> her putting back. By the same
                                        opportunity, I believe, the intermediate<lb/> Nos. of the
                                        Occident have arrived, tho I have not yet received them.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I regret to inform you that the Cholera<lb/> has
                                        been raging with unusual malignity in this
                                                  <placeName>Island</placeName> for the<lb/> last
                                        six weeks, to which fearful malady my lamented
                                                  father<add>?</add><lb/>
                                        <add>זצ"ל</add> fell a victim on <date>Tuesday Evening last
                                                  the 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> Inst. As the<lb/>
                                        <add>שבעה</add> is but just up, I have been unable to attend
                                        to anything<lb/> hence my non-receipt of the Occidents just
                                        arrived. I have handed<lb/> over the names of the
                                        subscribers to this valuable periodical to <persName>Mr
                                                  Lawton</persName><lb/> your agent, whose
                                                  <add>?</add> will enable him to attend to the
                                        pecuniary<lb/> part with success. Notwithstanding this, be
                                        assured I will not<lb/> slacken in my endeavors to obtain
                                        further subscribers thereto, as well<lb/> as to your
                                                  partnered<add>?</add> publication of the “Jewish
                                        Advocate.” Still, it is<lb/> my duty to tell you candidly, I
                                        do not apprehend any degree of success,<lb/> as the distress
                                        of our Community is beyond expression. For some time<lb/>
                                        (indeed since the appearance of the Cholera amongst us)
                                        Business has<lb/> been at a complete stand, and the means of
                                        the <hi rend="underline">few</hi> who are blessed</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>with worldly substance have been largely called on for the<lb/>
                                        <add>?</add> of their own as well as the <hi
                                                  rend="underline">General</hi> poor of the City.
                                        Large<lb/> Collections have been made both in the Synagogue
                                        as well as out<lb/> of doors. Notwithstanding, the great
                                        mass of our people are materially<lb/> altered in
                                        circumstances, so much so, that I fear the pecuniary<lb/>
                                        position of our synagogues will be much affected
                                        thereby.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">A Day of General Humiliation was appointed<lb/>
                                        and observed on <date>Friday the 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi>
                                                  Nov.</date> last, but owing to the<lb/> inclemency
                                        of the weather which prevented a great majority from<lb/>
                                        attending, the Governor appointed <date>Wednesday the 13<hi
                                                  rend="sup">th</hi></date> following for a<lb/>
                                        similar purpose. I need scarcely add lost days were
                                        religiously<lb/> observed by our people.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">There seems to be a desire manifested in<lb/>
                                        <placeName>Falmouth</placeName> for the establishment of a
                                        regular congregation, and the erection<lb/> of a synagogue,
                                        but I fear, that internal dissensions, chiefly relative<lb/>
                                        to <add>מנהג</add> are obstanly<add>?</add> to so desirable
                                        an end. Perhaps a few<lb/> remarks from your pen in the
                                        Occident might be serviceable.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I forgot to state that a “Hebrew Benevolent<lb/>
                                        Society” has been formed for the relief of our destitute
                                        Brethren<lb/> during the prevalence of the Cholera. It is to
                                        be hoped that when the<lb/> Almighty shall have, in His
                                        mercy, removed from us this “noisome<lb/> pestilence,” the
                                        association will not be suffered to fall to the ground.</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>Our friend <persName>B A Franklin</persName> takes a very active
                                        part in its<lb/> management.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I duly forwarded your letter to the
                                                  <persName>Reverend<lb/> A P Mendes</persName>,
                                        thro his father.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">With the assurance of my esteem and good
                                        wishes,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Believe me, my dear sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Yours very faithfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Henry S.
                                        Jacobs</persName>.</p>
                    </body>
